rComments: This Professor was a nightmare and by far the lowest point of my first semester at the University. The expectations for the course are unclear and the lectures are by no means enough information. He assumes you should know enough about religions to do well. You have to look for the information in the book and you will never find it. Avoid SRS1112!

As a fourth year student, I took this class as an optional mandatory course and overall it did not disappoint. The professor made the course very easy to understand the different religions without going far in-depth for beginners to religion. If you actually know the power points and actually study the readings then you should do well.

Nice guy. The way the grading is set up is nice, 3 midterms, each of them on one of the 4 units. The final exam is only worth a little bit more then the midterms and is on the 4th unit and has an essay that was cumulative on it. Pretty easy. The material isn't all that great but the way it is set up, sets you up for success !

Tells you everything you need to know in the lectures. Very interesting and engaging class, even brings in guest speakers to help connect the class to peoples lives. My only thing I did not like is no no Laptops rule, as someone how has insanely messy writing that I can barely read, this was the only thing that prevented full success.

Great guy BUT he gets off topic during lectures, puts questions on exams on topics that we don't cover during class, and treats you like a high school student (will kick you out if you're talking or on your phone). No need to attend lectures but go to the ones before a midterm (you have 3). This class made me lose interest in world religions lol

I took his class as an out of faculty elective but he quickly became my favourite prof. It is clear that he is passionate about his subject field and he really cares about his students. I would definitely recommend him as a professor!

Great professor, open to help and very kind. Wants everyone to succeed. I did find that the midterms were marked fairly hard and overall there's a lot of content. Definitely not an easy class, really need to work hard for a good mark. Need the textbook - all the midterms and exam covers its content

Professor de Bruyn is a great man - he's incredibly intelligent and really lovely on a personal level. However, his class material and lecturesseminars are boring. If you take a class with de Bruyn, I would suggest meeting with him in his office hours - he is incredibly helpful and you will probably learn more there than in class.

Hardly give any feedback on assignments, though his TA does almost all the marking. A little irrational when it comes to students talking, if I ask my neighbour a question about what he said, or if he sees a phone, he'll ask you to leave the class. Reminded me of high school.  Fair marker, tries to give you the highest grade possiblefair.

He is a great professor. I enjoyed his class, and his teaching style made it even more interesting. He is a great individual, and loves teaching. I would recommend his classes to anyone who likes Classics our Religions.

I took this class because I thought it'd be an easy elective. I was wrong. He rambles on about the most irrelevant subject matter and his lectures are extremely dull. There were questions on the exams we never touched on in any classes. Go to the lectures near the exams, read the textbook, and hope for the best

Prof. Debruyn is a great professor, but you have to take an interest in the class and do the work.  It also helps to discuss things with him after class during office hours.  That is where you will learn the most and witness his real personality.
Very boring lectures, I rarely went. Go to lectures near the exams, figure out what you need to know, and just study it.

World Religions I. Worst prof ever. He relys way too much on the textbook, which you need to memorize and spends so much time in class on irrelevant topics.  He seems nice though, but can't make up for his teaches. tests always seem like he's trying to trick you and just makes them so hard. AVOID if you can and Bon Chance if you can't!
Worst prof ever and does not know how to speak properly. Ruined world religions for me. Save yourself and do not take his class.
This is the most boring Professor I have ever had. Classes were painful to sit through, did not engage the class at all. Do not take this class!
Intro to World Religions- I got an A on the course, but he was not a good lecturer. He did not seem to know much about the material even though it is an introductory course.

He is an utter failure of an academic. He is unorganized and a horrendous lecturer and his knowledge of religious traditions fails to make it through his heavy curtain of slurred speech and monotone tangents. Subject matter should be interesting given the subject to which it explores, but this prof does a terrible job. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!

He made this class very difficult. He is a historian and seems to think everyone knows about all the random wars that happened 2000 years ago. He's the most painfully boring prof I have ever encountered and he's always having trouble with electronics. Be prepared to basically teach yourself the material.

This professor is one of the worst I have had in a while! In order to pass the course you need to be able to memorize the Torah/Bible/Qur'an... If you can't then don't take the course! He is monotone and stutters horrendously. Save yourself and drop the course!
EXCELLENT
This Guy is The MAN!!! god-like in most respects
To be honest, avoided most of my classes near the end. Very dry, and does alot of multiple choice pop quizzes as main evaluation. So not so good for those with learning disabilities.

I was really looking forward to studying Medieval history and this class turned me off. It was not the professor, rather the focus on religion that annoyed me. He is clear but his lectures aren't exactly stimulating. He's not a bad prof, but he definately isnt one of my favorites.

If you do not like just sitting a listening for three hours straight DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS WITH HIM.  I don't think he knows how to lecture in any way besides JUST talking.  He is incredibly boring in tone and it is so easy to fall asleep.  He uses annoying trick questions on exams as well.

I would have rather shoot myself in the face with a nail gun then attend this class. Boring, hard and not worth the time or effort. Again, I'd rather have shot myself in the FACE with a NAIL-GUN then write another paper or study for another test.

Prof. De Bruyn is a fantastic SRS teacher.  His courses are well organized and interesting.  It is important to go to all the lectures and to try to do most of the readings.  I would definately reccomend a class with him.
